posts.name: Taj Entabi
posts.cooked:
Today we did a test run of our new swerve robot, and at first the connection on the radio was very shoddy even though we connected it to a piece of aluminum on the exterior, powered through POE and backed up with direct power from the PDH . After deploying some test code, we found that the robot code indicator stayed red. We reflashed the rio and updated the AP and robot radio to 25.0.0, and nothing worked. Communication flashed between red and green at completely random intervals, and even a blank WPIlib template wouldnt make the robot code turn green.

Heres the test code we ran: https://github.com/FRC9706/Robot-2025/tree/CompExperimental

Anyone have any ideas about what might be causing this?

posts.name: Joseph Walters
posts.cooked:
What firmware are you putting on the radio?

25.0.0 is not a firmware name/number that is associated with the VH-109/would be a release FAR in the future.

The release version as of 3/29/25 is 1.3.0…

Additionally you should narrow down your variables.

Can you deploy tethered? Can you bring up the radio or Rio web pages? Does each device see the other and have the right IP address (visible through the Rio webpage or arp-a in command line when connected to the robot or for the radio via the network configuration tool for the VH radios)

posts.name: Jim Sokoloff
posts.cooked:
2.4GHz on that radio is broken and should be disabled to give a stable radio connection.

There’s 3 DIP switches underneath; turn off the one for 2.4GHz wifi.

posts.name: Sam
posts.cooked: How are you powering over POE? It’s recommended that if you’re using the RPM , you should not connect redundant power.

posts.name: Owen Flanagan
posts.cooked: Is this a new rio flash and if so did you remember to set your team number?

posts.name: garyk
posts.cooked:
Please look at https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/short-url/cTfoHJfLx2AjGYhpWiLpndfqKBY.pdf

for a radio wiring guide, it was put together by a Robot Inspector (“ RI ”) for inspections at competitions.

posts.name: Taj Entabi
posts.cooked: RPM means what in this context? (sorry, im a newbie)

posts.name: Taj Entabi
posts.cooked: Thanks, sorry I was thinking about the rio. Yes the radio firmware is 1.3.0. We did deploy tethered, and it worked fine. Untethered on radio, the arp-a only shows the IP sometimes. We found a weird solution somewhere in a dark corner of Chief Delphi, and switched the OS to Russian to avoid arabic numerals, which apparently breaks it… In any case, Robot code is still red.

posts.name: Sam
posts.cooked: RPM is the radio power module from rev.

posts.name: Fletcher
posts.cooked: Let’s start from the top. Can you please post a screenshot of the network config page of the roboRIO and the /status page of the VH-109.
